				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
...do you have any chance of repairing your faction with the Sarnaks[?]
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Yes.
<br />

<br />
I completely bottomed out my monk's sarnak faction (could not possibly get any worse with both sarnak factions) while camping the iksar betrayer for his epic pipe. He's now max ally with Brood of Di'Zok, and threatening to the Sarnak Collective.
<br />

<br />
Salts and skins are the only way to raise Sarnak Collective (unless Korocust and his buddies in 'dokB give a +hit), while salts, skins, and goblins give +faction to Brood.
<br />

<br />
It will take a <span style="font-weight: bold">long</span> time to raise the faction though. Somewhere in the vacinity of 3,500 positive hits. It's worth it though for those chords, and the final ring. Now if I can just find Drusella up twice (once for the monk, once for the mage).<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
Mistomeer C'Dyarnt
