			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1) Get a ranger friend with EQ/AM3/Headshot and a fast bow
<br />

<br />
2)Get out WoX
<br />

<br />
3)Gear up with Kedge or Walnan, and AC gear on pet
<br />

<br />
4)Go nuts
<br />

<br />

<br />
WoX can tank usually 3-4 mobs before I had to pop a heal at 61. With Ranger's regen and/or DPoC, just backoff for a second and you'll never have to heal. Ranger pulls, pet tanks, you can nuke as mana permits.
<br />

<br />
The great thing is that 80% of the mobs in here can be headshotted by the ranger, making you AA and faction with almost no work. It was actually pretty common to HS the casters before they stopped casting at spawn point. 
<br />

<br />
At 61 I actually made 20% regular XP an hour this way, fighting in the large room that looks like a figure 8 kindof, with a single named spawn point. 
<br />

<br />
After a few nights both the ranger and I were non-kos, and now I am warmly and the regular CoTH mage for Royals raids (if you do this, pre-call anklesmasher if it drops. A good way to get a great payment for the help, and most people won't mind you calling it before for your services. You also get to leech free xp while on the raid, just don't do any damage or anything) :D<br />_________________<br />Vaanen Aelwarr'n 
<br />
Mage of Torvonnilous
<br />
~Now with EPIC power!~</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
